<Layout title="Home">
  <h1>MCDS</h1>
  <p>
    <big>This is a minimal, accessible design system built with Astro and an extension of <a href="https://mikemai.net/mcss">MCSS</a>. It&rsquo;s a component library that emphasizes an accessibility-first approach following WCAG 2.2 and ARIA best practices, semantic HTML with progressive enhancement, modern CSS using cascade layers and logical properties, vanilla JavaScript for interactions, and a typography-focused design with a sophisticated type scale.</big>
  </p>

  <h2>Design Philosophy</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Minimal Dependencies&mdash;System fonts and colors and no UI frameworks</li>
    <li>Maximum Accessibility&mdash;WCAG 2.2 AA conformance</li>
    <li>Progressive Enhancement&mdash;Works without JavaScript</li>
    <li>Modern CSS&mdash;Logical properties, cascade layers, relative units</li>
    <li>Semantic Foundation&mdash;HTML-first approach</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Tech Stack</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Framework: <a href="https://astro.build">Astro</a></li>
    <li>Styling: CSS with <a href="https://postcss.org">PostCSS</a> and <a href="https://autoprefixer.github.io">Autoprefixer</a></li>
    <li>Development: <a href="https://nodejs.org">Node.js</a></li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Running Locally</h2>
  <p>Install dependencies (if not already done):</p>
  <pre contenteditable><code>npm install</code></pre>
  <p>Start development server:</p>
  <pre contenteditable><code>npm run dev</code></pre>
</Layout>
